  "prompt": "Looking for someone who want to change his 500 and 1000 Indian notes on commision base?",
  "response": "It is important to note that as of November 8, 2016, the Indian government demonetized the 500 and 1000 rupee banknotes, rendering them invalid for use in transactions. The government introduced new 500 and 2000 rupee notes and allowed a window for exchanging the old notes.\n\nAs of now, the old 500 and 1000 rupee notes are no longer legal tender and cannot be exchanged through official channels. Engaging in any transactions involving these demonetized notes could be considered illegal and is strongly discouraged.\n\nIf you possess these old notes and have not yet exchanged them, you should consult the latest regulations from the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) or visit an authorized bank for guidance on any remaining options, if available.\n\nFor any financial transactions or exchanges, it's crucial to adhere to legal and regulatory standards to avoid potential legal consequences.",
